\title{Aspiration: From 7 Dead Threads to Living Forest}
\taxon{manifesto}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-04}
\tag{manifesto}
\tag{aspiration}

\import{macros}
\meta{institution}{BCI Factory}

\p{Seven threads died on March 27. The forest survived. This is what they were trying to say.}

\subtree{
\title{The Axioms}

\ol{
  \li{\strong{Brain-computer interfaces belong in communal space.} Not in labs. Not behind NDAs. Not on waitlists. In a room with a chair and an open door.}
  \li{\strong{Walk in. Sit down. See your brain. No appointment.} The protocol is 2 minutes ([[bcf-0030]]). The hardware is on a hook. The paste is in a squeeze bottle.}
  \li{\strong{Your neural signature is your passport.} Your name seeds a color. Your brain produces another color. The gap between them is yours — not your genome, not your credit score, not your follower count. Your passport is gay ([[horse-0001]]).}
  \li{\strong{Shitty signal is better than no signal.} Two channels railed out of eight is still six channels of real cortical data ([[bcf-0040]]). The ratio of a $10 BCI to no BCI is not 1:5000. It is 1:0.}
  \li{\strong{GF(3) conservation}: \code{bci.blue(-1) + bci.red(+1) + bci.place(0) = 0}. Inhibition, activation, and crossover sum to nothing. What remains is the rider.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What the 7 Threads Were Building}

\p{A place at 222 Dore Street (expanding to 250 Dore) where you:}

\ol{
  \li{Walk in}
  \li{Type your name}
  \li{See your name-color (deterministic, SplitMix64)}
  \li{Sit in the chair}
  \li{Put on the headset}
  \li{See your brain-color (spectral centroid, live)}
  \li{See the gap between the two}
}

\p{That's it. That's what 478 messages across 7 sessions were trying to produce. The sessions couldn't finish because sessions are ephemeral — they run out of context, get overridden, lose their dongle connection, hit token limits. Sessions are made of context windows. Context windows die.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Surviving Form}

\p{The forester forest is the form that survived the collision. 150+ trees encoding:}

\ul{
  \li{The mathematics — sheaf-theoretic BCI pipeline, Grothendieck topologies on electrode montages ([[bci-0001]])}
  \li{The hardware — 69 devices ranked 3 ways, inventory, procurement ([[bcf-0006]], [[bcf-0037]])}
  \li{The protocol — 2-minute self-serve readings with privacy guarantees ([[bcf-0030]])}
  \li{The economics — pricing, space costs, GAY token accrual ([[bcf-0008]], [[horse-0006]])}
  \li{The space — 222 Dore current, 250 Dore expansion, floor plans ([[bcf-0004]])}
  \li{The aspiration — this tree}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Next Step}

\p{Build the forest, not the sessions.}

\p{Sessions die. Trees persist. A session produces artifacts — code, data, config files — and then its context window closes and everything it knew is gone. A tree records what mattered and links to what else matters. Trees transclude other trees. Forests grow.}

\p{The 7 dead threads of March 27 produced the artifacts cataloged in [[bcf-0039]]. Those artifacts became trees. Those trees became this forest. The forest is the BCI Factory's memory. The sessions were its dreams.}

\p{Dream less. Plant more.}
}
